    "htmlContent": "<h2>Hybridation challenges in Integrated assessment modeling for energy transition</h2>\n            <div class=\"attribution\">Generated by Cirdi on Thursday, July 10, 2025</div>\n            <div class=\"generation-stats\"><span> Tokens: 0 in, 2,409 out. LLM cost: 0.07 cent. Self hosting cost: 0.15 cent (H100 VPS hourly rate for 1.75s.). </span></div>\n            <div class=\"settings-stats\">Retrieval en mode vanilla limité à 10 segments. Génération avec mistral/mistral-small-latest limité à 1024 tokens out.</div>\n            <hr/>\n    <p>The challenges of hybridization in integrated assessment modeling for energy transition are multifaceted and have been extensively discussed in various studies. Here are some key points derived from the provided context:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><p><strong>Gap Between Policy Framing and Model Results</strong>: There is a noted gap between the framing of transition issues towards low carbon economies and the results brought by global integrated models. This gap highlights the need for better alignment between policy insights and model outcomes <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"74a7064b-1f64-5611-a6f2-def7cb6e7c49\"\n                              >[1a]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"4a227395-bb85-5197-97f4-41bc521e2606\"\n                              >[2a]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"a80759f7-a374-5cf2-8674-3afe62676d22\"\n                              >[2b]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"410b4fe7-fd69-52ce-b43e-1761706c548b\"\n                              >[1b]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"11398a36-3755-59e2-8257-078dd558c54f\"\n                              >[1c]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"2eced491-340e-51aa-84b6-daffb776177c\"\n                              >[2c]</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Methodological Issues</strong>: Building multi-sector energy-economy hybrid models involves several methodological challenges. These include integrating macroeconomic frameworks with engineering-based representations to improve the credibility of the assessments produced <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"74a7064b-1f64-5611-a6f2-def7cb6e7c49\"\n                              >[1a]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"4a227395-bb85-5197-97f4-41bc521e2606\"\n                              >[2a]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"a80759f7-a374-5cf2-8674-3afe62676d22\"\n                              >[2b]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"410b4fe7-fd69-52ce-b43e-1761706c548b\"\n                              >[1b]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"11398a36-3755-59e2-8257-078dd558c54f\"\n                              >[1c]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"2eced491-340e-51aa-84b6-daffb776177c\"\n                              >[2c]</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Limitations of Existing Tools</strong>: A guide of available model toolboxes is provided to better delimit the areas of competence of existing tools and to understand some of their limitations. This helps in identifying the strengths and weaknesses of current models <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"74a7064b-1f64-5611-a6f2-def7cb6e7c49\"\n                              >[1a]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"4a227395-bb85-5197-97f4-41bc521e2606\"\n                              >[2a]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"a80759f7-a374-5cf2-8674-3afe62676d22\"\n                              >[2b]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"410b4fe7-fd69-52ce-b43e-1761706c548b\"\n                              >[1b]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"11398a36-3755-59e2-8257-078dd558c54f\"\n                              >[1c]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"2eced491-340e-51aa-84b6-daffb776177c\"\n                              >[2c]</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Uncertainty Management</strong>: There is a lack of uncertainty management linked to models' alternative structures and conceptions. Historical model taxonomies are insufficient to inform the diversity of recent integrated and hybrid models' conceptions <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"11398a36-3755-59e2-8257-078dd558c54f\"\n                              >[1c]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"2eced491-340e-51aa-84b6-daffb776177c\"\n                              >[2c]</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Internal Vision of Models</strong>: A guide of integrated models based on their internal vision of energy-economy transformations and their integrated conception of the low carbon transition is introduced. This guide characterizes models and helps in understanding their internal mechanisms <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"11398a36-3755-59e2-8257-078dd558c54f\"\n                              >[1c]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"2eced491-340e-51aa-84b6-daffb776177c\"\n                              >[2c]</a>.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p><strong>Application to Specific Cases</strong>: The challenges are often discussed in the context of specific applications, such as the Brazilian case, which provides a practical perspective on the implementation of hybrid models <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"74a7064b-1f64-5611-a6f2-def7cb6e7c49\"\n                              >[1a]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"4a227395-bb85-5197-97f4-41bc521e2606\"\n                              >[2a]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"a80759f7-a374-5cf2-8674-3afe62676d22\"\n                              >[2b]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"410b4fe7-fd69-52ce-b43e-1761706c548b\"\n                              >[1b]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"11398a36-3755-59e2-8257-078dd558c54f\"\n                              >[1c]</a>, <a class=\"citation-bracket\"\n                              href=\"#cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\"\n                              data-chunk-id=\"2eced491-340e-51aa-84b6-daffb776177c\"\n                              >[2c]</a>.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>These points collectively highlight the complexities and challenges associated with hybridization in integrated assessment modeling for energy transition, emphasizing the need for improved methodologies, better alignment with policy goals, and more effective management of uncertainties.</p>\n\n        <div class=\"bibliography-container\">\n            <div class=\"bibliography-header\">\n                Pour en savoir plus:\n            </div>\n            \n        <div class=\"document-item\" id=\"cite-hal-tel-02923571-msg-1752138428514\">\n            <div class=\"document-number\" style=\"margin-right: 0.5em;\">1a, 1b, 1c</div>\n            <div class=\"document-content\">\n                <h4 class=\"document-title\"\n                    data-doc-title=\"Hybridization challenges in energy-economy integrated models and representation of the low carbon transition : An application to the Brazilian case\"\n                    data-doc-description=\"This thesis provides insights about the hybridization challenges in energy-economy integrated models and about the integrated representation of the low carbon transition, and proposes an application to the Brazilian case. Noting the existing gap between the framing of transition issues towards low carbon economies and the results brought by global integrated models, it provides a guide of the available model toolbox which brings a new view on the internal vision of models about energy-carbon-economy transformation pathways. This makes it possible to better delimit the areas of competence of existing tools and to understand some of their limitations. Our work especially underlies the relevance to work under a hybrid approach which articulates a macroeconomic framework with engineering based representations in order to improve the credibility of the assessments produced and we detail the methodological issues to build multi-sector energy-economy hybrid models. Part of the methodological principles are applied to build a tool to analyze the low carbon transition of the medium run in Brazil. We show how a carbon tax policy makes it possible to articulate several policy objectives until 2030 targeting purchasing power, competitiveness, employment and income distribution, beyond climate goals. Our diagnostic underlies the importance of the structural specifics of the energy-economy context in Brazil and of macroeconomic mechanisms linked to trade and labor market rigidities, which are often overlooked in existing studies. We eventually provide specific insights about the articulation between climate and oil policy in Brazil.\"\n                    data-doc-authors=\"Julien Lefevre (2016)\"\n                    data-doc-year=\"2016\"\n                    onmouseover=\"showTooltip(event, this)\"\n                    onmouseout=\"hideTooltip()\">\n                    Hybridization challenges in energy-economy integrated models and representation of the low carbon transition : An application to the Brazilian case\n                </h4>\n                <p class=\"document-authors\">Julien Lefevre (2016)</p>\n                <p class=\"document-links\">\n            <a href=\"https://hal.science/tel-02923571\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 flex items-center\">\n                <span class=\"mr-1\">🔗</span>\n                HALId: tel-02923571\n            </a>\n        </p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n        <div class=\"document-item\" id=\"cite-hal-tel-01685944-msg-1752138428514\">\n            <div class=\"document-number\" style=\"margin-right: 0.5em;\">2a, 2b, 2c</div>\n            <div class=\"document-content\">\n                <h4 class=\"document-title\"\n                    data-doc-title=\"Hybridization challenges in energy-economy integrated models and representation of the low carbon transition: An application to the Brazilian case\"\n                    data-doc-description=\"This thesis provides insights about the hybridization challenges in energy-economy integrated models and about the integrated representation of the low carbon transition, and proposes an application to the Brazilian case. Noting the existing gap between the framing of transition issues towards low carbon economies and the results brought by global integrated models, it provides a guide of the available model toolbox which brings a new view on the internal vision of models about energy-carbon-economy transformation pathways. This makes it possible to better delimit the areas of competence of existing tools and to understand some of their limitations. Our work especially underlies the relevance to work under a hybrid approach which articulates a macroeconomic framework with engineering based representations in order to improve the credibility of the assessments produced and we detail the methodological issues to build multi-sector energy-economy hybrid models. Part of the methodological principles are applied to build a tool to analyze the low carbon transition of the medium run in Brazil. We show how a carbon tax policy makes it possible to articulate several policy objectives until 2030 targeting purchasing power, competitiveness, employment and income distribution, beyond climate goals. Our diagnostic underlies the importance of the structural specifics of the energy-economy context in Brazil and of macroeconomic mechanisms linked to trade and labor market rigidities, which are often overlooked in existing studies. We eventually provide specific insights about the articulation between climate and oil policy in Brazil.\"\n                    data-doc-authors=\"Julien Lefevre (2016)\"\n                    data-doc-year=\"2016\"\n                    onmouseover=\"showTooltip(event, this)\"\n                    onmouseout=\"hideTooltip()\">\n                    Hybridization challenges in energy-economy integrated models and representation of the low carbon transition: An application to the Brazilian case\n                </h4>\n                <p class=\"document-authors\">Julien Lefevre (2016)</p>\n                <p class=\"document-links\">\n            <a href=\"https://hal.science/tel-01685944\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 flex items-center\">\n                <span class=\"mr-1\">🔗</span>\n                HALId: tel-01685944\n            </a>\n        </p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    \n        </div>\n    "
